Here is a super sweet video from our beloved Matilda (aka @crazyheadcomics), the independent artist who we collaborated with this month for our Mental Health Awareness campaign, including the Feelings Chart Magnet we've been including FREE with all orders of $60+ 💕

🎉  Tomorrow is Matilda's birthday! Happy Birthday from our Self-Care community, @crazyheadcomics! 🎂 Thank you for all the love and talent you share with us 🥰

🙊 To celebrate, we sent her a package with all of her new designs, and it was delightful to be invited to view her unboxing. It is always an honor to experience the joy of an artist holding their designs in their hands for the first time.

We hope you love this video as much as we did!! 😊

🙏🏼 It was such an honor to hold this space today. I really felt the community energy and love as we breathed. 

I am Sasha and I am one of the founders here @selfcareisforeveryone 💕 Meditation and breathing is one of the ways that I self-care for my mental health. I am not an expert in meditation ( by any means) but this is a space I come back to when I need to reconnect with my heart. 💕 Doing this practice with friends and community has been really healing for me and I invite you to join us as we spend time together sitting with our feelings. 

If you are watching this as a replay, stay as long as you wish. This space will always be available to you in our IGTV section! 

Use this time to connect with yourself however feels right. You can keep this live in the background as a reminder to breathe with us.✨

You deserve time to slow down and process your day. Take time to be with yourself, and listen to whatever you are experiencing internally. 

Happy Mental Health Awareness Month, sending you so much love 💕

According to the poll we took in our story yesterday, so many of you shared that you had never heard of Self- Care Day!! 💜

July 24th or 7/24, symbolizes that the benefits of self-care are experienced 24 hours a day, 7 days a week. How clever is that? :) 

We’re just excited to have a reason to celebrate self-care 🎉

🙃 Y’all voted for this one!! ‘YOUR FEELINGS ARE VALID’ is now LIVE! 

This one is for the days when the world just feels upside down and nothing seems to go right. 🙃 

All feelings are valid and all feelings are welcome. 💕

“I made this design with smiling faces because regardless of how I’m feeling I believe it’s important to still be kind & gentle with myself and others. The smiles on this design are also a reminder that you don’t know what someone is going through based on how they appear. Sending love and to anyone who feels like they have to hide their feelings with a smile. You are not alone.” - @sashaaronzon 

♥️

🪲- You have survived 100% of your worst days. 
🦋 - You are Good Enough.

#community

💕✨😊🙏

♥️ If you need support in a challenging time:

What you are experiencing can really impact your mental health and ability to focus. We wanted to include some resources of where you can reach out for support if it ever feels quite challenging. 🙏

All US residents can Text HOME to 741741 Crisis Text Line is available 24/7 to connect you with a trained crisis counselor ready to help you through any situation you’re finding challenging. This can range from school stress to coronavirus anxiety, depression to suicidal thoughts, and everything in between. A safe and confidential platform, Crisis Text Line can help you through your most difficult moments.

To find more resources (including inside or outside of the USA) check out our Mental Health Resources on our website. ♥️🙏 It’s okay to ask for help, you are not alone!!

Sending you all so much love ♥️🌈

node.text:
🧠 What does “Mental Health Matters” mean to you? (Ex: I’m allowed to have a mental health day, it’s okay to say no, it’s okay to take a break ) 

We love this reminder from @eljoart so much!! 💕🥺 Here’s how Eleanor started making art around mental health:

“I’ve always found it easier to articulate myself visually rather than verbally, and my relationship with my mental health has greatly influenced my art. I’ve had depression, anxiety and other issues for about 5 years. Initially I found it extremely difficult to put into words how I felt, let alone accept my emotions. During the darkest times, I found I was only truly honest in my artwork, and it helped me figure out what I was going through. I also explore the side effects of medication. For example, antidepressants made me shake a lot so I also ponder how movement is perceived. This led me to improve my relationship with myself while communicating honestly & understanding what wellbeing means to me. Now I create work in hope of changing the conversations and ideas around mental health, and to promote positive coping mechanisms.”

Visit our post from earlier today to learn more about Eleanor! 🥰

( 🎨 by @eljoart )

node.text:
We are so excited to spotlight @eljoart ♥️ AKA Eleanor Cowell, a painter and illustrator from the UK. Her work mostly explores her experiences with depression, as well as raising awareness and exploring conversations around mental health & social issues.

💕 Here’s what Eleanor does to practice self-care:

“I do a LOT of dancing, not good dancing more like shaking around but it’s a great way to transform negative energy. My self-care practices vary from running to drawing to inhaling chocolate, if that’s what I need that’s ok!! They’re all in the aim of reconnecting and being honest with myself about how I feel. I also conduct free Arts Wellness sessions on Zoom, which is for my benefit as much as everyone who comes along!”

Hope you all love @eljoart art as much as we do! 🥰
